This paper proposes a many-objective optimization algorithm that combines two interacting processes: cascade clustering and reference point incremental learning. The algorithm is designed to address the challenges of obtaining proximity while maintaining diversity for many-objective optimization problems. Given the focus on optimization and learning, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). However, the paper also involves clustering, sorting, and feedback, which are relevant to other sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
